TY  - JOUR
TI  - Congestion Tolls for Poisson Queuing Processes
AU  - Edelson, Noel M.
AU  - Hilderbrand, David K.
AB  - [The relationship between Pareto optimal (<tex-math>$\theta _{s}$</tex-math>) and revenue maximizing (<tex-math>$\theta _{r}$</tex-math>) tolls is examined for queuing models that permit balking. When customers have the same value for waiting time, <tex-math>$\theta _{s}\equiv \theta _{r}$</tex-math> provided the entrepreneur can impose a simple two-part tariff. With heterogeneous values for waiting time, <tex-math>$\theta _{r}$</tex-math> can be greater than, equal to, or less than <tex-math>$\theta _{s}$</tex-math>. Expanding the number of servers and charging multi-part tariffs are shown to be alternative methods for segmenting the market, and the welfare implications of these two strategies are explored.]
C1  - Full publication date: Jan., 1975
DB  - JSTOR
